---
# LLM Configuration
llm_provider: anthropic  # Options: anthropic, groq, openai
llm_model: claude-sonnet-4-5  # Model name for generated code

# Vector Store & Embeddings
vector_store: faiss  # Options: faiss, chroma
embeddings: huggingface  # Options: huggingface, openai

# Testing
test_framework: pytest  # Options: pytest

# Code Style
code_style: pydantic_v2  # Options: pydantic_v2, pydantic_v1
async_by_default: true  # Generate async code by default
include_type_hints: true  # Include type hints in generated code
include_docstrings: true  # Include docstrings in generated code

# Workflow Validation
auto_validate: false  # Automatically run workflow-validator after file changes
---

# LangGraph Development Settings

This file configures the langgraph-dev plugin for code generation and scaffolding.

## Usage

1. Copy this file to `.claude/langgraph-dev.local.md`
2. Customize the settings above to match your preferences
3. All settings are optional - the plugin uses sensible defaults

## Settings Explanation

### LLM Configuration
- **llm_provider**: Which LLM provider to use in generated code
  - `anthropic`: Anthropic Claude (recommended for this project)
  - `groq`: Groq LLMs (fast inference)
  - `openai`: OpenAI GPT models

- **llm_model**: Specific model name
  - Anthropic: `claude-sonnet-4-5`, `claude-opus-4`
  - Groq: `qwen-2.5-32b`, `llama-3.1-70b`
  - OpenAI: `gpt-4`, `gpt-3.5-turbo`

### Vector Store & Embeddings
- **vector_store**: Vector database for RAG implementations
  - `faiss`: Facebook AI Similarity Search (lightweight, local)
  - `chroma`: Chroma DB (more features, persistent)

- **embeddings**: Embedding model provider
  - `huggingface`: HuggingFace models (free, `all-MiniLM-L6-v2`)
  - `openai`: OpenAI embeddings (requires API key)

### Testing
- **test_framework**: Testing framework for generated tests
  - `pytest`: Standard Python testing (only option currently)

### Code Style
- **code_style**: Pydantic version for state schemas
  - `pydantic_v2`: Pydantic 2.x (recommended, modern)
  - `pydantic_v1`: Pydantic 1.x (legacy compatibility)

- **async_by_default**: Generate async code patterns
  - `true`: Use `async def`, `await`, `ainvoke()`
  - `false`: Use synchronous patterns

- **include_type_hints**: Add type annotations
  - `true`: Full type hints on all functions/methods
  - `false`: Minimal type hints (only where required)

- **include_docstrings**: Add documentation strings
  - `true`: Docstrings for all functions/classes
  - `false`: No docstrings (code only)

### Workflow Validation
- **auto_validate**: Run workflow-validator automatically
  - `true`: Validate after any Write/Edit on StateGraph files
  - `false`: Only validate when explicitly invoked

## Examples

### Configuration for Anthropic Claude + FAISS
```yaml
llm_provider: anthropic
llm_model: claude-sonnet-4-5
vector_store: faiss
embeddings: huggingface
async_by_default: true
```

### Configuration for Groq + Chroma
```yaml
llm_provider: groq
llm_model: qwen-2.5-32b
vector_store: chroma
embeddings: openai
async_by_default: true
```

### Minimal Configuration (All Defaults)
```yaml
# Empty frontmatter uses all defaults
```

## Notes

- This file is ignored by git (`.claude/*.local.md` in .gitignore)
- Changes take effect immediately for new command invocations
- Invalid settings fall back to defaults with warnings
- You can override settings per-command using arguments
